article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay 76, Oakland, Mich. 75
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Mike Schachtner had 23 points and seven rebounds and hit the game-clinching free throw with 10.9 seconds left as Wisconsin-Green Bay opened its season with a 76-75 win over Oakland (Michigan) on Friday night. Oakland's Johnathon Jones hit a 3-pointer with 0.5 left to make it a one-point game, but the Phoenix was able to inbound the ball and run out the clock. Rahmon Fletcher finished with 14 points for Green Bay and Ryan Tillema came off the bench to add 11 points. Grizzlies reserve guard Brandon Cassise finished with a game-high 26 points on 9-of-18 shooting. Jones had 14 points and Derick Nelson added 10 points and eight rebounds. The Phoenix (1-0) turned the tables on the Grizzlies after last year's season opener, in which Oakland began with a 18-2 run and never trailed in a 16-point win. This time it was Green Bay who got off to the hot start, using an early 15-0 run to build a 23-7 lead midway through the first half. Oakland (0-1) battled back, taking a 46-45 lead with a 15-3 spurt to begin the second half. The game was back and forth from that point on. Green Bay used a 10-0 run to take a 58-50 lead but the Grizzlies responded with another 15-3 run to reclaim the lead. The win was the fifth straight home-opening victory for the Phoenix.
